vulnerabilities.title: Out-of-bounds Read
vulnerabilities.description:
## Overview
File does not properly utilize the do_core_note function in readelf.c in
      libmagic.a.A remote attacker could send a specially crafted ELF file possibly
      resulting in a Denial of Service condition.

## References
- [CONFIRM](https://github.com/file/file/commit/a642587a9c9e2dd7feacdf513c3643ce26ad3c22)
- [GENTOO](https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/201806-08)
- [NVD](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2018-10360)
- [SUSE](http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2019-03/msg00027.html)
- [SUSE](http://lists.opensuse.org/opensuse-security-announce/2019-04/msg00053.html)
- [UBUNTU](https://usn.ubuntu.com/3686-1/)
- [UBUNTU](https://usn.ubuntu.com/3686-2/)
vulnerabilities.name: file/libmagic
vulnerabilities.dockerfileInstruction: RUN apk add --no-cache bash sudo nano sudo zip bzip2 fontconfig wget curl

vulnerabilities.title: Out-of-bounds Write
vulnerabilities.description:
## Overview
musl libc through 1.1.23 has an x87 floating-point stack adjustment imbalance, related to the math/i386/ directory. In some cases, use of this library could introduce out-of-bounds writes that are not present in an application's source code.

## References
- [ADVISORY](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2019-14697)
- [Debian Security Tracker](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-14697)
- [Gentoo Security Advisory](https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/202003-13)
- [MISC](https://www.openwall.com/lists/musl/2019/08/06/1)
- [OSS security Advisory](http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2019/08/06/4)
vulnerabilities.name: musl/musl
vulnerabilities.dockerfileInstruction: RUN apk add --no-cache bash sudo nano sudo zip bzip2 fontconfig wget curl

- [ADVISORY](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2019-14697)
- [Debian Security Tracker](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-14697)
- [Gentoo Security Advisory](https://security.gentoo.org/glsa/202003-13)
- [MISC](https://www.openwall.com/lists/musl/2019/08/06/1)
- [OSS security Advisory](http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2019/08/06/4)
